They live a long time, they grow slowly.

00:54:02.083 --> 00:54:05.951
It may take 25 or 30
years for them to mature.

00:54:05.951 --> 00:54:09.256
We don't raise 25 year
old chickens or cows.

00:54:09.256 --> 00:54:11.900
You know we like to turn
'em over pretty fast,

00:54:11.900 --> 00:54:14.203
and yet we take wildlife from the sea,

00:54:14.203 --> 00:54:19.203
sharks and creatures that
again live a long time,

00:54:20.802 --> 00:54:24.108
might have taken 20 or 25 years to grow,

00:54:24.108 --> 00:54:26.779
and yet we extract them thinking,

00:54:26.779 --> 00:54:28.861
huh, you know they're free.

00:54:28.861 --> 00:54:31.180
Let's just go get them,

00:54:31.180 --> 00:54:35.600
and it's exactly what
we've been doing at a pace

00:54:35.600 --> 00:54:40.600
that outstrips the capacity
of these creatures to recover.

00:54:41.038 --> 00:54:45.583
Whether it's sharks, or tunas,

00:54:46.642 --> 00:54:51.642
where is our capacity as
brilliant creatures that we are,

00:54:52.347 --> 00:54:57.162
to think of a tuna fish
is good only in a sandwich

00:54:57.162 --> 00:55:01.250
or in a salad, or sushi, or sashimi.

